1. How to Run the BFS Code
Open Python in your device
Copy and paste the entire BFS code into a new file
Save the file.
Run the program .

2. Main Components
bfs(graph, start) → Main function that performs BFS.
graph → Adjacency list (dictionary) showing connections.
start → Starting vertex (e.g., 'A').

3. How to Use the Code (Step-by-Step)
  1.Define your graph
    Create connections using the edges list (undirected graph).
  2.Build the adjacency list
    The code automatically converts edges into a graph.
  3.Call the BFS function
    "result = bfs(graph, 'A')" 
    "print("BFS visit order:", result)"
  4.Run the program
The code will print the order in which nodes are visited.
